### Krishak Backend API Tests

### 1. Register a Farmer
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Karim Mia",
  "email": "karim@example.com",
  "phone": "01712345678",
  "password": "farmer123",
  "role": "farmer",
  "farmLocation": {
    "village": "Rampur",
    "thana": "Savar",
    "district": "Dhaka"
  }
}

###

### 2. Register a Buyer
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rahman Ahmed",
  "email": "rahman@example.com",
  "phone": "01812345678",
  "password": "buyer123",
  "role": "buyer"
}

###

### 3. Login
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "karim@example.com",
  "password": "farmer123"
}

###

### 4. Get Current User (Replace TOKEN with actual token from login)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

###

### 5. Get Profile
GET http://localhost:5000/api/users/profile
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

###

### 6. Update Profile
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/users/profile
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Karim Mia Updated",
  "phone": "01712345679",
  "farmLocation": {
    "village": "Rampur",
    "thana": "Savar",
    "district": "Dhaka",
    "coordinates": {
      "lat": 23.8103,
      "lng": 90.4125
    }
  }
}

